# Document Map

## Purpose

This repository uses a documentation-first structure. Each major document exists for a distinct reason.

## Documents

- `README.md`: quick orientation and project summary
- `AGENTS.md`: repository collaboration rules for agent workflows
- `CLAUDE.md`: Claude Code-specific adaptation notes
- `docs/domain-overview.md`: domain language and scope summary
- `docs/architecture.md`: high-level repository and system shape
- `docs/roadmap.md`: staged direction and planned maturation
- `docs/constraints.md`: boundaries, assumptions, and explicit non-goals

## Rule

If a document does not have a distinct purpose, it should not be added.
